The NFy Standard

Symbols

Check Mark

This symbol indicates that the described feature is required for an app to be up to date.

Red X

This symbol indicates that the described feature is either:

  • No longer supported, deprecated
  • No longer being required.

Warning Sign

This symbol indicates that the described feature(s) are planned to be implemented in future. Discarding this warning is not recommended, as you will need to implement specified features in the near future.

Songs

Play

  • Requirement Level -

Playing songs should be implemented with one song buffer to play any songs, and when the play button is pressed, load the current selected song and play it.

All NFy apps should have one song buffer, more than one is deprecated behaviour. Asynchronous buffers are not allowed. (Issue with NFy.js as well)

Formats & Playing

  • Requirement Level - (This feature will require .wav to be supported in the future, with .mp3 support still in construction.)

Loading songs should load a .ogg file called the song. (preferrably support for all 3, mp3, wav, AND ogg.)

Then, after reading it, itll play the song and move a Progress bar (not required), and preferrably display timestamps for the user.

UI

Hints

  • Requirement Level - (This feature will be required in the future.)

Hints such as Open Songs Directory, or just any opening of directories for setup, is recommended, and soon to be required.

Any buttons that will aid in the setup of songs, can aid in user support, and also make your NFy Client more fun to use.

Progress Bar

  • Requirement Level -

Using a progress bar is not required for an NFy app, but is recommended to remind the user to know where they are at what point in the song.

Keys

  • Requirement Level - (This feature will be required in the future.)

The keys NOW are <, Enter, and >.

Before, they were J, K, and L, but as UI changes caused the keys to be deprecated, now the keys are Left arrow, enter, and the right arrow.

Playlist

Format

  • Requirement Level - (The new V3 API will contain ground-breaking changes, beware!)

The V2 API contains the songs key, while the v1 API uses the playlists_songs key.

That is the difference between NFy Monos playlists, and NFys playlists. And if you tried it, it would have a chance at probably crashing.

Shuffling

  • Requirement Level -

Shuffling playlists is not required, but like the progress bar, will aid in making your application more fun for everyone to use.

Shuffling is the term for when you move around array elements randomly.

array = [1,2,3]
array.shuffle()

print array

# => [2,3,1]

Playing

  • Requirement Level -

As of now, the way playing will work is that you will keep playing, and then at the end, it looks for the next song in the array, and plays it.

There are some utilities to aid in the array algorithm, such as: NFyPlaylists.js

News

  • Requirement Level - (News is no longer required, and is deprecated behaviour.)

Setup

Directories

  • Requirement Level -

The only directory that needs to be created is songs, if your app contains playlist support, you need to use the playlists directory as well.
